post_text:
The J.O. Combs Unified School District is pleased to offer a limited number of scholarships for low-income families in need of quality child care. Made available through Quality First funding from First Things First of Arizona, the District is offering 14 full-time, or 28 part-time, scholarships for students ages three to five to participate in early learning programs.

Scholarships may be used for Combs Kinder Prep or Combs Young Coyotes pre-school at Ranch Elementary. Both programs provide a foundation for early childhood learning and equip students to be better prepared to start Kindergarten. Kinder Prep is open to 4-5 year olds, and is taught by a certified teacher, while Young Coyotes is open to 3-5 year olds and provides opportunities to grow socially, emotionally, and academically through hands on activities.

Families who wish to learn more or apply may do so by contacting Tammy Carley, Community Education Supervisor, here https://bit.ly/3h88mBD

Official statement: Today we were informed that a report was made to the Pinal County Sheriff‚Äôs Office (PCSO) regarding a Combs High School student who posted self-threatening content on Snapchat. PCSO has worked closely with Combs High School administration to promptly investigate the matter, and have determined that no credible threat was made or written.

The safety of students and staff is the highest priority of the J.O. Combs Unified School District, and families would be notified directly should a substantiated safety concern ever arise.

Media inquiries can be directed to Kayla Fulmer at 480-252-4482.
